<article>
<header>
$if(date)$
<p class="byline"><strong>Due Date:</strong> $date$ at 11:59PM (Central Time)</p>
<hr />
$endif$
<h3 class="unnumbered" id="instructions">Instructions</h3>
<p>This assignment must be submitted on Gradescope. You will upload your
answers as a PDF. Make sure your work is clearly labeled. <strong>When
you upload, you must match each problem with the page(s) it is
on</strong>. <strong>If you do not match a problem to the pages it is
on, a 10% penalty will be applied to the grade for that
problem</strong>. You must upload correct answers to the mandatory
problems to receive full credit for the assignment.</p>
<p>In general, you are graded on both the clarity and accuracy of your
work. Your solution should be clear enough that someone in the class who
had not seen the problem before would understand it. <strong>Problem set
answers must be legible</strong>. <em>Illegible work <strong>will not be
graded</strong>.</em> We cannot award points for solutions that we
cannot easily read. If you are typing your answers, make sure you use
the correct symbols. You can use an equation editor in Google Docs or MS
Word, or you can use Overleaf and the LaTeX template we have provided
(see the LaTeX Resources on Canvas for help on how to use LaTeX). Please
make sure to read over your work before submitting it! (just because
it's typed does not always mean it's legible).</p>
<p>We sometimes describe approximately how long our explanations are.
These are intended to help you understand approximately how much detail
we are expecting. You are allowed to have longer explanations, but
explanations significantly longer than necessary may receive
deductions.</p>
<p><strong>This assignment is individual</strong>. Offering or receiving
any kind of unauthorized or unacknowledged assistance (including
searching for solutions online or using Generative AI tools) is a
violation of the University's academic integrity policies, will result
in a grade of zero for the assignment, and will be subject to
disciplinary action.</p>
<p><em>Please see the <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1QRFpQPQMHIuzrkTJmHBaoMCrqfb6MxhTpAck3sRsmXM/edit?usp=sharing">Course
Syllabus</a> for the full <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1QRFpQPQMHIuzrkTJmHBaoMCrqfb6MxhTpAck3sRsmXM/edit?tab=t.ks06hwu1mwin">homework
formatting</a>, <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1QRFpQPQMHIuzrkTJmHBaoMCrqfb6MxhTpAck3sRsmXM/edit?tab=t.d2yzqh52rqkq#heading=h.uwfbp6k89x3i">collaboration</a>,
and <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1QRFpQPQMHIuzrkTJmHBaoMCrqfb6MxhTpAck3sRsmXM/edit?tab=t.ks06hwu1mwin">late
policies</a>.</em></p>
</header>
$body$
